### Hadith 1:602

*Narrated Abu Dhar:*

We were in the company of the Prophet on a journey and the Mu'adhdhin
wanted to pronounce the Adhan for the (Zuhr) prayer. The Prophet said to
him, "Let it become cooler." Then he again wanted to pronounce the Adhan
but the Prophet; said to him, "Let it become cooler." The Mu'adh-dhin
again wanted to pronounce the Adhan for the prayer but the Prophet said,
"Let it become cooler," till the shadows of the hillocks become equal to
their sizes. The Prophet added, "The severity of the heat is from the
raging of Hell."

